  <section id="about-us">
    <h2>About Ichagaki Boys High School</h2>
    <p>
      Ichagaki Boys High School is an extra county school located in Murang'a County, Kenya. Established in 1963, it is one of the best-performing schools in the county. Notable alumni include the CEO of Equity Bank. The school is led by Principal Paul Thangwa, deputized by Gachanja. With over 40 teaching personnel and more than 750 students, our motto is "Education Empowers."
    </p>
    <p>
      Our mission is to provide holistic education where students can study without consideration of race, tribe, or religion. Our teachers maintain personal contact with their students, creating an enabling study environment. Ichagaki Boys High School is committed to being corruption-free.
    </p>
  </section>

